(1115, 64688, '21 Jump Street', 'They thought the streets were mean. Then they went back to high school.', 2012, 'In high school, Schmidt was a dork and Jenko was the popular jock. After graduation, both of them joined the police force and ended up as partners riding bicycles in the city park. Since they are young and look like high school students, they are assigned to an undercover unit to infiltrate a drug ring that is supplying high school students synthetic drugs.', 6.7, 62.714027, 'en', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/8v3Sqv9UcIUC4ebmpKWROqPBINZ.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BjRs18rV1FI'),
(1116, 509, 'Notting Hill', 'Can the most famous film star in the world fall for the man on the street?', 1999, 'The British comedy from director Roger Michell tells the love story between a famous actress and a simple book seller from London. A look into the attempt for famous people to have a personal and private life and the ramifications that follow. Nominated for three Golden Globes in 2000.', 7, 28.96915, 'en', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/k7cwPG5sVmCumxKZCukyu3SbyjG.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bMrOp79dM74'),
