(2802, 11658, 'Tae Guk Gi: The Brotherhood of War', '', 2004, 'In 1950, in South Korea, shoe-shiner Jin-tae Lee and his 18-year-old old student brother, Jin-seok Lee, form a poor but happy family with their mother, Jin-tae''s fiancé Young-shin Kim, and her young sisters. Jin-tae and his mother are tough workers, who sacrifice themselves to send Jin-seok to the university. When North Korea invades the South, the family escapes to a relative''s house in the country, but along their journey, Jin-seok is forced to join the army to fight in the front, and Jin-tae enlists too to protect his young brother. The commander promises Jin-tae that if he gets a medal he would release his brother, and Jin-tae becomes the braver soldier in the company. Along the bloody war between brothers, the relationship of Jin-seok with his older brother deteriorates leading to a dramatic and tragic end.', 7.4, 9.572705, 'ko', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/vyG8qpimh3XSlxc6OmPq8LJRJl.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nnx2CjhHADM'),
