(3745, 8337, 'They Live', 'Who are they? And what do they want?', 1988, 'Nada, a down-on-his-luck construction worker, discovers a pair of special sunglasses. Wearing them, he is able to see the world as it really is: people being bombarded by media and government with messages like "Stay Asleep", "No Imagination", "Submit to Authority". Even scarier is that he is able to see that some usually normal-looking people are in fact ugly aliens in charge of the massive campaign to keep humans subdued.', 7.1, 29.852608, 'en', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/ngnybFTuopfbfmmEeX9jjBQQmF6.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vSVQ975eTBI'),
